006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Rue","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["French: topographic name for someone who lived beside a road, track, or pathway, Old French <i>rue</i> (from Latin <i>ruga</i> ‘crease, fold’).","Shortened form of American French   Larue   2, itself an altered form of French   Leroux  .","English: from Middle English <i>rew</i> (Old English <i>rāw</i>) ‘row’. The surname may be topographic, signifying someone who lived by a hedgerow or in a row of houses in a street, or habitational, from a place so named, such as Rewe (Devon), Rew Farm in Rockbeare (Devon), and Rew in Malborough (Devon). See also   Rawe   1 and   Rowe  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Larue","meanings":["French: topographic name for someone who lived beside a road, track, or pathway, Old French <i>rue</i> (see   Rue  ), with fused feminine definite article <i>la</i>; or a habitational name from La Rue, the name of several places in various parts of France, of the same origin. Compare   Delarue  .","Altered form of French   Leroux  . Compare   Rue   2.","History: This surname (see 2 above) is listed in the (US) National Huguenot Society's register of qualified Huguenot ancestors (in the form <i>La Rue</i>, along with the variant <i>Larew</i> and the original form <i>Le Roux</i>) and also in the similar register of the Huguenot Society of America."]},{"name":"Rew","meanings":["English (Devon): variant of   Rue  .","Americanized form of German   Ruh  ."]},{"name":"Ruen","meanings":["Norwegian: habitational name from a farm so named, among others in Hadeland, from Old Norse <i>ruth</i> ‘clearing’. Compare   Rue  .","German: variant of <b>Ruhn</b>, from a short form of an ancient Germanic personal name such as <i>Ruomald</i>. The surname <i>Ruen</i> is virtually non-existing in Germany.","Possibly also an altered form of German <b>Rühen</b>, a shortened form of <b>Rüden</b> (see   Ruden  ). The surname <i>Rühen</i> is very rare in Germany."]}]},{"name":"Annella","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Elaborated form of   Anne .  It is favoured in the Highlands of Scotland."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"Annella de Rue was born in 1380, in Lindsell, Essex, England, United Kingdom. She had at least 1 daughter with Sir Cooley Cowley. She died in 1441, in her hometown, at the age of 61."},"et":{"1380–1441":"1380–1441","1400–1460":"1400–1460","1440–1505":"1440–1505","1400":"1400","1441":"1441","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","1380":"1380","1505":"1505","Lindsell, Essex, England":"Lindsell, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Lindsell,,Essex,England":"Lindsell, Essex, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1380–1441":"1380–1441","1400–1460":"1400–1460","1440–1505":"1440–1505","1400":"1400","1441":"1441","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","1380":"1380","1505":"1505","Lindsell, Essex, England":"Lindsell, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Lindsell,,Essex,England":"Lindsell, Essex, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1380–1441":"1380–1441","1400–1460":"1400–1460","1440–1505":"1440–1505","1400":"1400","1441":"1441","1440":"1440","1460":"1460","1380":"1380","1505":"1505","Lindsell, Essex, England":"Lindsell, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","Lindsell,,Essex,England":"Lindsell, Essex, Angleterre, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Annella de Rue est née en 